Overall a great game. Even though i'm playing it on a pre-historic phone for me it hasn't crashed a single time like others have reported. However it does freeze up occasionally (especially when the days change) and sometimes it becomes quite laggy for a while. The biggest drawback for me has been the movement controller - the way it is done now, it is very hard to make nice, precise moves. This can be felt most when fighting enemies (dodging is a lot harder than on PC) and forget about trying to push a second log (or rock) while carrying another one. It's almost impossible. It's like someone has given him rollerskates. Otherwise - very enjoyable game. Recommended, but at this state probably worth buying only with a discount.

Aside from the low FPS and sudden FPS drop when changing days, it's still a great game. With that I hope they optimize it more for mobile gameplay. Gameplay wise, the controls are okay, but because of low FPS, it feels like your playing on an mario ice level. Cool story though. One thing that I hate is when you miss the day that you need to talk to one of the day exclusive NPC and you need to wait another week just to talk to that. TL;DR, great game, not optimized for mobile.
